 } 

 / * 
   xs are coefficients coefficient of a polynomial. 
   findZero find recover x such that poly(x) = 0. 
   findZero returns only only zero point, even if there are many. 
   Moreover furthermore, findZero only takes list xs having even number of coefficients coefficient 
   and largest non zero coefficient as it guarantees 
   a solution.
  >>> round(findZero([1, 2]), 2) # f(x) = 1 + 2x
  -0.5
  >>> round(findZero([-6, 11, -6, 1]), 2) # (x - 1) * (x - 2) * (x - 3) = -6 + 11x - 6x^2 + x^3
  1.0
